title: For Sale:  .30 CAL M1 CARBINE WITH ALL USGI PARTS  ***SOLD***
postcontent:
Of course there is a down side...It' not WWII vintage...Everything on this exceptional carbine is USGI except for the receiver and barrel shroud, butt plate and maybe the front sight (may be a replacement part)...This vintage classic is a National Ord. carbine with a copper top...It was manufactured around 1963 and since the serial number is 10,2xx, I am assuming from what I've read that this was made at the beginning of Northern Ord.'s production cycle...Which means that they used all USGI parts until they used up all of the surplus parts from WWII...And after that they began making there own. So basically this is a spectacular rifle...It's a shooter with great accuracy...Plus this is only one of the few carbines that will be legal if the Nationalistic Democratic Party has there way...
The following stamps are on it:

Receiver:  National Ord. serial 10,2xx  (Copper Top)   
Trigger assy: Inland  (Copper Colored)
Front sling/stock clamp:  Q                 
Stock:  46D
Bolt:  .U.                                          
Rear Strap Post:  SI
Operating rod:  Z                              
Rear Sight:  H (in a shield)
(2) 15 Rnd Magazines:  IA and  B (in a circle)
Barrel:  6 grooved with no markings visible. (Possibly Marlin or Winchester)
Front Sight:  No visible markings.

So if all of you M1 experts have any info I'd appreciate it

Plus it was made in the USA...That's if you still count California.
So make a reasonable offer and this baby can be yours.
